---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="How to Make Every Customer Touch Point Shoppable - parcelLab"
  description="Learn how to turn post-purchase communications into revenue drivers with branded tracking, product recommendations, and shoppable touchpoints."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Research</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">How to Make Every Customer Touch Point Shoppable</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2022-06-20">June 20, 2022</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>5 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Retailers have optimized marketing channels to drive sales through shoppable social posts and live video shopping. However, the post-purchase phase presents significant untapped opportunities. Research indicates that 53% of shoppers feel that the post-purchase stage is the most emotional part of the shopping journey.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Opportunity</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--ink)]">Post-purchase order notifications achieve click-through rates as high as 70%. If you're not optimizing these touchpoints, you're leaving money on the table.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Use Post-Purchase Comms to Drive Web Traffic</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Order confirmations and dispatch notifications receive high engagement. Rather than sending generic emails, brands should adopt branded designs encouraging website visits.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Case Study: 11teamsports</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            The company integrated branded post-purchase emails with links to key website pages, allowing shoppers to explore sales and vouchers.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">19% revenue increase</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">8% increase in basket size</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">3.5% boost in repeat purchases</strong></span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Make Relevant Product Recommendations in Order Tracking Messages</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Case Study: Fashionette</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Fashionette enhanced order tracking emails with related products and content, plus implemented a rating tool for customer feedback.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">75% growth in customer web traffic</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">45% increase in reviews</strong></span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Implement a Branded Order Tracking Portal</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Research shows 81% of shoppers track their orders two or more times during fulfillment. However, analysis of leading fashion retailers revealed only 19% offer immersive embedded tracking experiences; 59% rely on third-party websites, while 22% use carrier pages.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Case Study: Watches of Switzerland</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            The brand partnered with parcelLab to launch a branded order status page, maintaining brand consistency while driving webstore traffic.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Every post-purchase touchpoint is an opportunity to drive revenue. From branded order confirmations to immersive tracking portals, the brands winning in retail are those making every interaction shoppable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
